'''Augustus O. Bourn''' ([[October 1]], [[1834]] - [[January 28]], [[1925]]) was an [[United States|American]] politician and a former [[governor of Rhode Island]].

Bourn was born in [[Providence, Rhode Island]] on [[October 1]], [[1834]]. He graduated from [[Brown University]] and later established a successful career in Rubber business. He held the governor's office from [[May 29]], [[1883]] to [[May 26]], [[1885]]. During his administration,  a constitutional amendment was proposed to extend suffrage to naturalized citizens. Later the constitutional amendment became well-know as the Bourn Amendment. Bourn was an active member of the [[Freemasons]].[http://politicalgraveyard.com/geo/RI/masons.html]

He died on [[January 28]], [[1925]].

== Sources ==
* Sobel, Robert and John Raimo. ''Biographical Directory of the Governors of the United States, 1789-1978''. Greenwood Press, 1988. ISBN 0-313-28093-2

